article_id:2743,category_name:News,title_name:Regarding an Issue Causing an Additional Summon to Be Performed When Tapping "Retry" in the Summon Screen Error Pop-up [Update],image_path:,message:<div><span style="color: rgb(41, 105, 176);"><strong>[<span class="local_date" data-local_date="1641880800"></span>]</strong></span><br>We will distribute the wyrmite, summon vouchers, or diamantium that was consumed when performing an additional summon (by selecting Try Again) from around <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640930820"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640932320"></span> to all players who performed those summons.<br><br>Affected players can claim these items from their goodie box.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div><div><br></div><hr><div>We have confirmed an issue occurring from approximately <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640930820"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640932320"></span> where a &quot;Failed to connect to the server&quot; pop-up would sometimes appear while performing a summon, and tapping &quot;Retry&quot; would result in an additional summon being performed.<br><br>We have confirmed that the summoned adventurers and dragons were correctly obtained even if the summon animation for this additional summon didn&#39;t play. You can check your Summon History from the Help/Support section of the Menu.<br><br>This issue has now been resolved.<br><br>As a token of our appreciation for your understanding, we will send a gift of one tenfold summon voucher to all players who performed a summon between <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640930820"></span> and <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1640932320"></span>.<br>This gift can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after reception.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1641016800,update_time1641880784